* ============================================================
*  Littelfuse PolySwitch 72R Series PPTC Model
*  NGSpice Behavioral Model
*  Datasheet: Rev VL 07/30/25
*
*  Model topology:
*    - Thermal node (V_temp) driven by self-heating: P = I^2 * R(T)
*    - Thermal RC: C_th (thermal mass) + R_th (thermal resistance to ambient)
*    - Resistance R(T): low below Curie point (~130 C), high above
*    - PPTC trip modeled as exponential R(T) characteristic
*
*  Subcircuit ports:
*    A  K  TAMB
*    A   = anode  (current enters here)
*    K   = cathode
*    TAMB= ambient temperature node (connect to GND for 20 degC ambient,
*          or drive with a voltage = delta_T above 20 degC)
*
*  Usage example:
*    .include "72R_PPTC.lib"
*    XFUSE A K TAMB 72R090X
*    VTAMB TAMB 0 DC 0    ; 20 degC ambient
*
*  Temperature derating:
*    The TAMB node accepts a DC voltage where 1V = 1 degC ABOVE 20 degC.
*    Example: 40 degC ambient -> VTAMB TAMB 0 DC 20
*    Example: -20 degC ambient -> VTAMB TAMB 0 DC -40
*
*  Parameters (from datasheet electrical characteristics):
*    I_HOLD = hold current at 20 degC (A)
*    I_TRIP = trip current at 20 degC (A)  [= 2 * I_HOLD]
*    R_MIN  = minimum cold resistance (Ohm)
*    R_1MAX = max resistance 1hr after trip (Ohm)
*    PD_TYP = typical tripped-state dissipation (W)
*    V_MAX  = 72 Vdc (all variants)
*    I_MAX  = 40 A  (all variants)
*
*  Thermal model parameters:
*    T_CURIE = ~130 degC  (PPTC crystal transition temperature)
*    R_TH    = thermal resistance to ambient (degC/W), estimated from
*              Pd_typ: T_surface_max=125C, T_amb=20C, so R_th ~ 105/Pd_typ
*    C_TH    = thermal capacitance (J/degC), estimated to reproduce
*              the datasheet time-to-trip at the specified test current.
*              Formula: C_th ~ I_trip^2 * R_cold * t_trip / (T_curie - T_amb)
*
*  Resistance model:
*    R_cold (T < T_curie) = R_min * exp(alpha * (T - 20))
*    R_hot  (T > T_curie) = R_1max * exp(beta  * (T - T_curie))
*    Blended with a smooth sigmoid: R(T) = R_cold + (R_hot-R_cold)*sig(T-T_curie)
*    sig(x) = 1/(1+exp(-k*x)), k=0.5 for a ~4 degC transition band
*
*  NOTE: This is a simplified single-pole thermal model.
*        Multi-pulse and repetitive fault behavior may not be accurate.
*        Always verify in your application per datasheet warning.
* ============================================================

* ------------------------------------------------------------
*  72R020X  Ihold=0.20A  Itrip=0.40A  Rmin=1.830 R1max=4.400 Pd=0.41W
* ------------------------------------------------------------
.subckt 72R020X A K TAMB
.param Ihold=0.20 Rmin=1.830 R1max=4.400 Pdtyp=0.41
.param Tcurie=130 Tamb_ref=20
.param Rth={105/Pdtyp}
.param Cth={4*Ihold*Ihold*Rmin*5/(Tcurie-Tamb_ref)}
.param alpha=0.02  beta=0.10  ksig=0.5
* Thermal node: Vtemp = temperature rise above Tamb_ref (in degC)
* Self-heating current source: P = V(A,K)^2 / R = I^2*R, injected into Cth node
* We use a B-source to compute instantaneous power
* Thermal node 'Tj' holds junction temperature
Cth_node Tj 0 {Cth} IC=0
Rth_node Tj TAMB {Rth}
* Power injection: I_heat = V(A,K)*I(Vsense) [power in watts]
* We use a voltage-controlled current source measuring current through the device
Vsense Aint A DC 0
Bheat 0 Tj I = V(Aint,K)*I(Vsense)
* Temperature: Tdev = Tj + TAMB + Tamb_ref  (degC)
* Resistance: R(Tdev) using smooth sigmoid blend
* Expressed as voltage-controlled resistor via B-source
* R_eff = Rmin*exp(alpha*(Tdev-20)) + (R1max*exp(beta*(Tdev-Tcurie))-Rmin*exp(alpha*(Tdev-20))) / (1+exp(-ksig*(Tdev-Tcurie)))
Bres Aint K V = V(Aint,K) - I(Vsense)*( {Rmin}*exp({alpha}*(V(Tj)+V(TAMB)+{Tamb_ref}-{Tamb_ref})) + ({R1max}*exp({beta}*(V(Tj)+V(TAMB)+{Tamb_ref}-{Tcurie})) - {Rmin}*exp({alpha}*(V(Tj)+V(TAMB)+{Tamb_ref}-{Tamb_ref}))) / (1+exp(-{ksig}*(V(Tj)+V(TAMB)+{Tamb_ref}-{Tcurie}))) )
.ends 72R020X

* ------------------------------------------------------------
*  72R030X  Ihold=0.30A  Itrip=0.60A  Rmin=0.880 R1max=2.100 Pd=0.49W
* ------------------------------------------------------------
.subckt 72R030X A K TAMB
.param Ihold=0.30 Rmin=0.880 R1max=2.100 Pdtyp=0.49
.param Tcurie=130 Tamb_ref=20
.param Rth={105/Pdtyp}
